      "titleText": "The Terminal & Shell",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 52,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "You'll hear words like terminal, console, shell, command thrown around constantly. To beginners it sounds spooky — the real power lives here. GUIs are fine for comfort, but true control belongs to the CLI.\nCommon shells: bash, zsh, fish.",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [
        "Term  ::  What it means",
        "Terminal  ::  The app you open to type commands — your window into the system",
        "Shell  ::  Lives inside the terminal; takes your commands and tells the kernel what to do",
        "Console  ::  Old-school term for a direct system interface — often used interchangeably with terminal",
        "GUI  ::  Graphical user interface — point, click, drag",
        "CLI  ::  Command line interface — type commands, automate, script"
      ],
